# URL Functionality Demo

This example demonstrates how to use URLs in Meld directives.

## URL Embedding Examples

### Embedding content from a URL

@embed(url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/main/README.md", allowURLs=true)

### Embedding with custom URL options

@embed(url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/main/README.md", 
  allowURLs=true, 
  urlOptions={
    allowedProtocols: ["https"],
    allowedDomains: ["raw.githubusercontent.com"],
    maxResponseSize: 1048576,  // 1MB
    timeout: 10000  // 10 seconds
  }
)

### Embedding a specific section

@embed(url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/main/README.md", 
  allowURLs=true,
  section="Installation"
)

## URL Import Examples

### Importing variables from a URL

@import(url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/main/examples/demo.mld", allowURLs=true)

### Using imported variables

After importing from the URL, you can use the variables:

{{greeting}}

## Using URL with path parameter

The URL functionality also works when using the path parameter with allowURLs=true:

@embed(path="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anthropics/claude-code/main/README.md", allowURLs=true)